*.orig.*
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision

# Google Play service-account key (used by eas.json submit.production.android).
# Never commit it.
google-service-account.json
# NOTE: GoogleService-Info*.plist / google-services*.json (Firebase CLIENT config
# for FCM) are intentionally COMMITTED, not ignored. They hold only client-side,
# bundle-id-restricted values (API_KEY, GCM_SENDER_ID, PROJECT_ID, GOOGLE_APP_ID)
# that ship inside the app binary anyway — Google designs them to be public. They
# must be in the repo so LOCAL EAS builds (`eas build --local`) work: EAS builds
# from the committed tarball, and the GOOGLE_SERVICES_PLIST file SECRET is not
# materialised for local builds (only cloud). The real secrets (APNs key,
# service-account JSON) stay server-side / ignored.

# Metro
.metro-health-check*

